summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2006 JEEP COMMANDER. WHILE DRIVING 65 MPH THE VEHICLE STALLED WITHOUT ANY PRIOR WARNINGS. AS A CONSEQUENCE THERE WAS AN INCREASED RISK FOR A VEHICLE CRASH.  THE VEHICLE WAS TOWED TO A LOCAL REPAIR FACILITY, IN WHICH A MECHANIC STATED THAT THE TRANSMISSION CAUSED THE FAILURE. NO REPAIRS WERE MADE. THE CURRENT AND FAILURE MILEAGES WERE 60000.
